1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,169
We learn in different ways, I said.

2
00:00:03,440 --> 00:00:07,490
I think you can learn a real success lesson from this experience.

3
00:00:07,840 --> 00:00:12,609
When you used your pony in there, your conscience bothered you terribly.

4
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:17,010
This gave you a guilt complex that in turn broke your confidence.

5
00:00:17,280 --> 00:00:20,290
As you expressed it, you went to pieces.

6
00:00:20,720 --> 00:00:27,409
Most of the time, Paul, this matter of right and wrong is approached from a moral or religious standpoint.

7
00:00:27,680 --> 00:00:33,090
Now understand, I'm not here to preach to you, give you a sermon about right and wrong.

8
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:35,330
But let's look at the practical side.

9
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:40,369
When you do anything that goes contrary to your conscience, you feel guilty,

10
00:00:40,560 --> 00:00:43,970
and this guilty feeling jams your thought processes.

11
00:00:44,160 --> 00:00:48,290
You can't think straight because your mind is asking, will I get caught?

12
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:49,889
Will I get caught?

13
00:00:50,480 --> 00:00:57,010
Paul, I continued, you wanted an A so badly, you did something you knew was wrong.

14
00:00:57,440 --> 00:01:01,169
There are many times in life when you'll want to make an A so badly,

15
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:05,250
you'll be tempted to do something that is contrary to your conscience.

16
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:13,730
For example, someday you may want to make a sale so badly you'll think of deliberately misleading the customer to buy,

17
00:01:13,920 --> 00:01:15,409
and you may succeed.

18
00:01:15,520 --> 00:01:17,169
But here's what will happen.

19
00:01:17,440 --> 00:01:22,530
Your guilty feeling will grab hold of you, and the next time you see your customer,

20
00:01:22,560 --> 00:01:25,010
you'll be self-conscious, ill at ease.

21
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:29,090
You'll be wondering, has he discovered that I put something over?

22
00:01:29,439 --> 00:01:33,730
Your presentation will be ineffective because you can't concentrate.

23
00:01:33,999 --> 00:01:39,570
Chances are you'll never make the second, third, fourth, and the many repeat sales.

24
00:01:39,759 --> 00:01:46,929
In the long run, making that sale using tactics that hurt your conscience will cost you a lot of income.

25
00:01:47,520 --> 00:02:00,690
I went on and pointed out to Paul how an occasional business or professional man loses his grip because of an intense fear that his wife will learn about a secret love affair he is having with another woman.

26
00:02:02,319 --> 00:02:03,650
Will she find out?

27
00:02:03,650 --> 00:02:03,650
Will she find out?

28
00:02:03,839 --> 00:02:09,810
eats away the man's confidence until he can't do a good job at work or in the home.

29
00:02:10,239 --> 00:02:16,049
I reminded Paul that many criminals are captured not because any clues point to them,

30
00:02:16,080 --> 00:02:19,090
but because they act guilty and self-conscious.

31
00:02:19,359 --> 00:02:22,929
Their guilt-feeling puts them on the suspect list.

32
00:02:23,679 --> 00:02:29,570
There is within each of us a desire to be right, think right, and act right.

33
00:02:29,759 --> 00:02:34,369
When we go against that desire, we put a cancer in our conscience.

34
00:02:34,639 --> 00:02:39,009
This cancer grows and grows by eating away at our confidence.

35
00:02:39,279 --> 00:02:44,290
Avoid doing anything that will cause you to ask yourself, will I get caught?

36
00:02:44,399 --> 00:02:45,730
Will they find out?

37
00:02:45,839 --> 00:02:47,330
Will I get away with it?

38
00:02:47,759 --> 00:02:52,369
Don't try to make an A if it means violating your confidence.

